                                    XPath
     Absolute XPath
     Relative XPath
     Relative + Absolute XPath
     
Relative XPath
//

1 = Finding element with tagname
//a
//img
//input
//select
//span

2 = Finding element with attribute and value
case sensitive
' ' and " " allowed (Single & Double quotes allowed)
//tagname[@attribute='value'] 
//input[@id='email1']
//input[@id="email1"]
//button[@type="submit"]
//button[@class="submit-btn"]

3 = Finding element with Multiple attribute and value
Using and
//tagname[@attribute1='value1' and @attribute2='value2']
ex: //input[@id="email1" and @placeholder='Email']

Using or
//tagname[@attribute1='value1' or @attribute2='value2']
ex: //input[@id="email1" or @placeholder='Email']


4 = Index based XPath
    (Xpath)[index]
    (//a)[6]
    
5 = contains function
    //tagname[contains(@attribute,'value')]
    //input[contains(@id,'email')]
    //input[contains(@id,'e')]
    //input[contains(@type,'pass')]
    //a[contains(@href,'youtube')]
    //a[contains(@href,'twitter')]

6 = Text function
     //tagname[text()='Text to find']
     //a[text()='Practise']
     //a[text()='New user? Signup']
     //h2[text()='Connect with us']
     //*[text()='Connect with us']
     
 
7 = Test function with contains
    //tagname[contains(text(),'text to find')]
    //a[contains(text(),'Practise')]
    //a[contains(text(),'Prac')]
    

What is the diff b/w 
   //a[text()='Practise']
   //a[normalize-space()='Practise']
   
Answer = in normalize-space() : No need to give text which has before or after space
       = in text()            : We need to give exact text even if it has before or after space
       

